---
description: Documenting comments
globs: src/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: true
---

- When writing comments, the file itself starts with a block comment containing a short description of the file's overview. This block comments requires tag "@updatedAt" with today's system date in the YYYY-MM-DD format. The system date can be defined by running the script in @cursor_current_date.ts

- When updating a file check for the block comment at the start of the file. If one is not there, add it.

- Creating or updating files are required to have its "@updatedAt" to be updated to today's date in the YYYY-MM-DD format.
